<Action id="35573" issue="17672" author="tkuhrt" type="comment" created="2017-11-28 15:54:29.0" updateauthor="tkuhrt" updated="2017-11-28 15:54:29.0"> <body><! CDATA Uploaded results from 11/27 scan. Here are the highlights: * There are 3 non-Apache components still in the codebase, two under MIT and one under a Zlib-style license. These are all permissive licenses which will likely be acceptable to the Governing Board. But they will still require exception approvals from the GB, per Hyperledger's IP Policy. * There remain about 300 files in the repo that don't contain an Apache-2.0 or CC-BY-4.0 license within the file itself. These do not require exception approval, but would likely be mentioned in the license report for the committee/board as an area for future improvement. * We would recommend that the community looks at adding SPDX short-form identifiers to individual files, as a quicker and more efficient way to add licensing details. * Also, for this report, we are now counting separately any files that are completely empty (e.g., fully empty __init__.py files). These are now listed separately in the report from other files with content but no license info.  ></body> </Action>
